## üîß Step-by-Step Setup

### 1. Set Up Azure Speech Service

#### a. Create a Speech Resource

- Go to [Azure Portal](https://portal.azure.com/)
- Navigate to **Create a resource ‚Üí AI + Machine Learning ‚Üí Speech**
- Fill in:
  - **Subscription**: Your Azure subscription
  - **Resource Group**: Create or select existing
  - **Region**: Choose closest to your Genesys region (e.g., `Central India`)
  - **Pricing Tier**: Standard (F0 for free tier if eligible)

#### b. Retrieve Keys and Endpoint

- After deployment, go to the Speech resource
- Copy:
  - **Key 1** (or Key 2)
  - **Region** (e.g., `centralindia`)
  - **Endpoint** (e.g., `https://centralindia.api.cognitive.microsoft.com/`)

---

### 2. Configure Genesys Cloud Integration

#### a. Install Azure STT Integration

- Log in to [Genesys Cloud Admin](https://apps.mypurecloud.com/)
- Go to **Admin ‚Üí Integrations**
- Search for ‚ÄúAzure Speech-to-Text‚Äù in AppFoundry
- Click **Install**

#### b. Configure Credentials

- During setup, provide:
  - **Subscription Key** (from Azure)
  - **Region** (e.g., `centralindia`)
  - **Endpoint** (optional if region is provided)

#### c. Set Language and Audio Settings

- Choose supported language (e.g., `en-IN` for Indian English)
- Set audio sampling rate (e.g., 8000 Hz for telephony)
- Optionally configure **custom phrases** in Azure Speech Studio

---

### 3. Use in Architect Flows

#### a. Open Architect

- Go to **Admin ‚Üí Architect**
- Select or create a **Bot Flow** or **Inbound Call Flow**

#### b. Add Speech-to-Text Action

- Insert a **Speech Recognition** or **Bot Input** action
- Select the Azure STT integration
- Map the audio input to a variable
- Use the transcribed text in decision logic or bot intents

---

### 4. Test and Validate

- Deploy a test flow with voice input
- Use real-world audio samples to validate transcription
- Monitor logs in Genesys and Azure Portal

